Have you ever had the feeling associated with buyer's remorse? I did at this place. It was my first time at this restaurant. I ordered a banh mi sandwich 🥪 to try their food out before coming back for other entrees. What a mistake that was.  Cost of the sandwich $8.50 + tax, and short of the $10 minimum requirement on a credit card purchase.   I asked for a water bottle, thinking that the cost of that would have satisfied the requirement.  They didn't have water bottles.  After pondering about what to order, I decided to ordered get a water cup & paid $1.50 for it!   $10 requirement met. Onto the sandwich.  How can you go wrong with a banh mi?  Plenty here. It starts with the bread, and the bread here seems stale and hard.  Although it had some of the veggies found in a traditional sandwich, the meat is not flavorful, but rather bland. I wanted to like this place after reading the reviews, but now probably won't return.  What a letdown........not recommended.

My boyfriend and I went to dinner at Little Vietnam on a Groupon voucher. So we got the most expensive appetizer-- a vegetable-filled crepe ($9), two salads (all were $8) two entrees (beef with asparagus and catfish in a clay pot) and dessert. The appetizer was the best part of the meal. The salads were fine, though they didn't seem worth $8 to me. There were two desserts on the menu, but neither was available, so we got tapioca, which was OK.  Now about the entrees.  Mine (catfish) was so salty that I couldn't eat it. I took it home and even with the addition of many vegetables, it was only marginally edible. And I actually like a good bit of salt on my food! My boyfriend's beef was bland, and almost as salty.  I mention the prices because the Groupon ad said the value was up to $63 and there was NO WAY that was true. But that really wasn't the issue. I'd like to think the salt problem was an abberation, but I would never take the chance, since the rest of the meal wasn't really anything special, even at a somewhat reduced cost.
